            "Small"
        ],
        "Contractor|HaulCargo_SingleToMulti": [
            "Greetings, \n\nSeems like <EM4>[Location|Address]</EM4> currently has some <EM4>4 SCU</EM4> or smaller cargo that needs to be separated and delivered to a few different spots. \n\nDROP OFF LOCATIONS (ANY ORDER)\n\n- Freight elevator at <EM4>[Destination|Address]</EM4>\n- Freight elevator at <EM4>[Destination1|Address]</EM4>\n\nDrop-offs can be done in whatever order works best for you.  \n\nBy the way, we strongly encourage contractors to bring a <EM4>handheld tractor beam</EM4> along.   \n\nCovalex Independent Contractors\n\nChase Hewitt\nJr. Logistics Coordinator\nCovalex Shipping  \n'Anything you need, anywhere you need it.'\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\nCovalex Shipping is a limited liability corporation. To encourage timely deliveries and prevent fraud on cargo hauls, Covalex Shipping will set a delivery time limit and upon expiration, any undelivered cargo will be considered stolen and treated as such. Total payment will be prorated according to the percentage of cargo successfully delivered.",
            "Hey, \n\nI\u2019ve a multi-stop run here that needs to be done. Good news is that all of the cargo is <EM4>4 SCU</EM4> or smaller and can be picked up from a freight elevator at <EM4>[Location|Address]</EM4>. The drop offs are spread across a few locations, but can be done in any order.     \n\nDROP OFF LOCATIONS (ANY ORDER)\n\n- Freight elevator at <EM4>[Destination|Address]</EM4>\n- Freight elevator at <EM4>[Destination1|Address]</EM4> \n\nBy the way, we strongly encourage contractors to bring a <EM4>handheld tractor beam</EM4> along.    \n\nCovalex Independent Contractors\n\nChase Hewitt\nJr. Logistics Coordinator\nCovalex Shipping  \n'Anything you need, anywhere you need it.'\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\nCovalex Shipping is a limited liability corporation. To encourage timely deliveries and prevent fraud on cargo hauls, Covalex Shipping will set a delivery time limit and upon expiration, any undelivered cargo will be considered stolen and treated as such. Total payment will be prorated according to the percentage of cargo successfully delivered.",
            "Hello, \n\nInterested in knocking out a few runs at once? \n\nThere\u2019s a load of cargo (<EM4>4 SCU</EM4> or smaller) waiting at a freight elevator in <EM4>[Location|Address]</EM4> that needs to be delivered to the following spots:\n\nDROP OFF LOCATIONS (ANY ORDER)\n\n- Freight elevator at <EM4>[Destination|Address]</EM4>\n- Freight elevator at <EM4>[Destination1|Address]</EM4>\n\nFeel free to route plan the drop-offs as you see fit.\n\nBy the way, we strongly encourage contractors to bring a <EM4>handheld tractor beam</EM4> along.   \n\nCovalex Independent Contractors\n\nChase Hewitt\nJr. Logistics Coordinator\nCovalex Shipping  \n'Anything you need, anywhere you need it.'\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\nCovalex Shipping is a limited liability corporation. To encourage timely deliveries and prevent fraud on cargo hauls, Covalex Shipping will set a delivery time limit and upon expiration, any undelivered cargo will be considered stolen and treated as such. Total payment will be prorated according to the percentage of cargo successfully delivered."
        ],
